	{{#content "region-a"}}
	<div class="block block-size-a">
		<h1 class="title-stylesheet">Scroll To</h1>

		<h2 class="subtitle-stylesheet">Scroll To example functionality <small><code>.scroll-to</code></small></h2>
		<p><em>This functionality will allow you to scroll to an element on click or automatically from the query string in the url</em></p>

		<p>
			<a href="#div-a" class="scroll-to-action">
				Traditional scroll to element based on href
			</a>
		</p>

		<p>
			<a href="#div-a" data-scrollto-target="#div-b" class="scroll-to-action">
				Scroll to element based on data attribute
			</a>
		</p>

		<p>
			<a href="#div-a" data-scrollto-speed="2000" class="scroll-to-action">
				Scroll to element with scroll speed specified
			</a>
		</p>

		<p>
			<a href="scroll-to.html?scrollto=div-b">
				Scroll to element on load via querystring
			</a>
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="block block-size-a">
		<h2 class="subtitle-stylesheet">Implementation information</h2>
		<h3 class="beta">To use scroll to:</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>To use via a link/button click a class of 'scroll-to-action' is needed on the link</li>
			<li>It will default to the id found in the href unless there is a data attribute of 'data-scrollto-target' that specified the elements id that should be scrolled to</li>
			<li>The default scroll speed is set in the JS (500) but this can be overridden via a data attribute of 'data-scrollto-speed'</li>
			<li>To scroll to an element on page load just add the querystring 'scrollto' with the elements id, e.g. 'page.html?scrollto=div-a'</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="beta">The relevant files:</h3>
		<pre>
			<code>
src/
|
|- assets/
|  |- scripts/
|      |- modules/
|        |- scrollto.js
|- pages/
|  |- scroll-to.hbs
			</code>
		</pre>
	</div>

